about.description:
psutil (process and system utilities) is a cross-platform library for
retrieving information on running processes and system utilization (CPU,
memory, disks, network) in Python. It is useful mainly for system
monitoring, profiling and limiting process resources and management of
running processes.
about.summary: A cross-platform process and system utilities module for Python

raw_meta_yaml:
schema_version: 1

context:
  version: 7.1.2
  sha256: aa225cdde1335ff9684708ee8c72650f6598d5ed2114b9a7c5802030b1785018

package:
  name: psutil
  version: ${{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.org/packages/source/p/psutil/psutil-${{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: ${{ sha256 }}

build:
  number: 0
  script:
    # macOS renamed this variable, but it is `NULL` in either case.
    # Workaround the missing definition by setting it to `0`.
    #
    # xref: https://github.com/giampaolo/psutil/issues/2354
    - if: osx
      then: export CFLAGS="${CFLAGS} -DkIOMainPortDefault=0"
    - ${{ PYTHON }} -m pip install --ignore-installed --no-deps .

requirements:
  build:
    - if: build_platform != target_platform
      then:
        - python
        - cross-python_${{ target_platform }}
    - ${{ compiler("c") }}
    - ${{ stdlib("c") }}
  host:
    - python
    - pip
    - setuptools >=43
    - wheel
  run:
    - python

tests:
  - python:
      imports:
        - psutil
        - if: linux
          then: psutil._psutil_linux
        - if: osx
          then: psutil._psutil_osx
        - if: win
          then: psutil._psutil_windows
        - psutil.tests

about:
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: A cross-platform process and system utilities module for Python
  description: |
    psutil (process and system utilities) is a cross-platform library for
    retrieving information on running processes and system utilization (CPU,
    memory, disks, network) in Python. It is useful mainly for system
    monitoring, profiling and limiting process resources and management of
    running processes.
  homepage: https://github.com/giampaolo/psutil
  repository: https://github.com/giampaolo/psutil
  documentation: https://psutil.readthedocs.io

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - jan-janssen
    - gqmelo
    - jakirkham
    - pelson
    - nehaljwani
